peopleAlsoAsk.question: How do you identify an Ayres rocking horse?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: One of the most distinguishing features of an Ayres rocking horse is the finely carved head and neck. The horses often have well-defined facial expressions, with open mouths and teeth. The ears are typically upright, and the nostrils and eyes are carefully sculpted for a realistic appearance.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: What year was the rocking horse made?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: The earliest one known to still exist is said to have belonged to King Charles I and dates from C1610. This type of rocking horse was developed through the next couple of centuries with the heads and bodies becoming more sophisticated and ornately carved and painted.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: What age is a rocking horse?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: A rocking horse might be a legend of the playroom, but when is it safe to introduce one to your child? This can depend on the kind of rocking horse you choose. A plush rocking horse with a backrest can be fun for your little one from the age of twelve months up, just in time for those toddler times!
